entry.content:

entry.title: [Device Posture] Move device posture implementation out of services/
entry.content:
It's becoming clear that the posture is not a global state. On Android

the posture is tied to an Activity : for example an Android Activity can

be on an external screen or two Chrome instances side by side and Android does not return the physical posture of the device. While right now Windows is a global state we can imagine scenarios like this where the "logical" posture doesn't match the physical posture.



This patch moves the device_posture mojo implementation out of services/. This means that now it is attached to a given web content. This allows us to simplify some of the implementation now that we can assume the receivers are from the same web content.



Also now that we are in the content/ layer we can directly hook into the device posture classes to implement the viewport segments support in RWHA.



Bug: 1517764

entry.title: [iOS] Perform a more robust check for password fields
entry.content:
The `isOnPasswordField` check was only checking if a field was

obfuscated to confirm that a field is a password field. This

causes websites which obfuscate other fields (such as credit card

number fields) to get incorrect or missing suggestions for those

fields. This CL adds an extra verification that if a field is

confirmed by field prediction to not be a password field, then

we don't interpret this field as a password field.

entry.title: Fix address cleanups for syncing users
entry.content:
See crbug.com/1517515#c1 for context. This CL fixes the problem by

looking at SyncService::GetDownloadStatusFor() in SyncServiceObserver:: OnStateChanged(), as explained in [1].



It restructures the code in the following way:

- Merges AddressDataCleaner::MaybeCleanupAddressData()

MaybeCleanupAddressDataAfterSyncChange() to a single

MaybeCleanupAddressData(sync_service).

This function is called after the PDM's initial load has finished and

again in PDM::OnStateChanged() (SyncServiceObserver implementation).

- MaybeCleanupAddressData(sync_service) determines whether the code

should wait for sync based on the sync_service. It further ensures

that clean-ups are called at most once (since OnStateChanged() might

be called many times).



This CL doesn't yet fix the problem that deduplication likely runs too

early after sync has started: After changes were synced down, they are

written to AutofillTable - the PDM needs to asynchronously reload them

before the cleanup logic can use it. This has likely not finished yet by

the time OnStateChanged() is called.

A follow-up CL will take care of this.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:components/sync/service/sync_service.h;l=544-546;drc=c60fa2587518257f0f3a4a38bfabaf0ecfa29eea

entry.title: Copy FormData::child_frames_ into FormStructure.
entry.content:
This field is used in `FormData::DeepEqual`, and in

`BrowserAutofillManager::ShouldTriggerRefill` this method is

called with a `FormData` recreated from a `FormStructure`.

Loosing this property leads to constant `false` from the `DeepEqual`

method and unnecessarily scheduled refilling for pages with iframes.



In this CL crrev.com/c/5036442 the refill triggering logic was moved

from the renderer to browser process. The same `DeepEqual` was used,

but it worked with `FormData` directly, while now it is converted from

`FormStructure` (where the `child_frames` field was missing).



It partially fixes the associated ticket by reducing the number of

events by a factor of 2.

entry.title: [URL] Support non-special URLs in Resolve()
entry.content:
Implement correct support for non-special URLs in gurl::Resolve() and

other functions, which are used on resolving a relative URL on a given

base URL.



Example:



Prior to this change:



> new URL("path", "git://host/") => throws an invalid URL error



After this change:



> new URL("path", "git://host/") => "git://host/path""



The feature is currently guarded by the flag.



This CL adds several parameterized unit tests to test flag-dependent

behaviors. Currently flag-independent behaviors are not tested with

the flag. I will revisit this later.



Though this CL introduces new expectation files for virtual tests,

there is no regression and the total number of test failures has

decreased. I use rebaseline cl tool and accept the result as is. It

seems there are several expectation files across different platforms,

accumulated over time.

entry.title: [LCPP] Remove unnecessary if conditions to call SetLCPPHint()
entry.content:
This is a refactroring CL to simplify the condition when/what to set

LCPP hint data.



|lcpp_hint| is originally set by `MaybeSetLCPPNavigationHint()` in the

LoadingPredictorTabHelper class, from the browser process. This only set

hint data when LCPP features are enabled, or `IsInOutermostMainFrame()`,

or `IsSameDocument()`. Otherwise |lcpp_hint| is nullptr. So, we don't

have to check `IsOutermostMainFrame()` in

`RenderFrameImpl::CommitNavigationWithParams()`.



I'm also skeptical if we should check `lcpp_enable_perf_improvements`

param here. If the param returns true, this doesn't set LCPP data.

I believe this is not intentional.

entry.title: Always reset LCPCriticalPathPredictor on navigation
entry.content:
Before this CL, LCPCriticalPathPredictor kept its state from the

previous navigation if the frame was reused. This CL fixes this behavior

by always resetting LCPCriticalPathPredictor on navigation.



Currently, inheriting the previous navigation states in

LCPCriticalPathPredictor causes the following problems.



- lcp_element_locators_ and lcp_element_locator_strings_ can accumulate

the elements if the

kLCPCriticalPathPredictorEnableElementLocatorPerformanceImprovements

parameter is false. This means that any features that don't enable

this flag can accumulate ElementLocator. This implies the following

features can have negative effects caused by this.

kLCPScriptObserver, kLCPPFontURLPredictor, kLCPPLazyLoadImagePreload,

kDelayAsyncScriptExecution, kHttpDiskCachePrewarming,

kLCPPAutoPreconnectLcpOrigin.



- The is_lcp_candidate_found_ flag seems not to be reset to false on new

navigation. This means that maybe MayRunPredictedCallbacks() is

skipped for some cases.

entry.title: Fix non-device ChromeOS chrome::DIR_CRASH_DUMPS
entry.content:
This restricts use of /var/log/{chrome,lacros} for DIR_CRASH_DUMPS to

IS_CHROMEOS_DEVICE builds. This lets us use DIR_CRASH_DUMPS on a local

linux-chromeos build. Providing a value for chrome::DIR_CRASH_DUMPS is

necessary for initializing crashpad. Without this change a local

is_chromeos build will fail if --enable-crashpad is provided.



Fixing this is necessary to ultimately remove --enable-crashpad (and

default it to true) without breaking local development and bots that

don't run on device. Looks like local development was still using the

breakpad flow.

entry.title: Introduce devtools_instrumentation::WillCreateURLLoaderFactoryParams
entry.content:
Preparation for

https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/5150529

and subsequent CLs to merge `devtools_instrumentation` call sites,

so that the unified method `url_loader_factory::Create()`

can invoke `devtools_instrumentation`

by `WillCreateURLLoaderFactoryParams::Run()`,

while the callers of `url_loader_factory::Create()`

create context-specific `WillCreateURLLoaderFactoryParams`,

instead of calling context-specific `WillCreateURLLoaderFactory*()`

methods directly.



This CL makes some callers to pass non-null `factory_chainer`

(for uniformity) where `nullptr` was used previously.

This doesn't change the behavior, because those callers pass

non-null FactoryOverride, and in such cases `factory_chainer` is

anyway not used.
